  <h1>User Cost Accounting Framework</h1>
  <section>
    <h2>About This Project</h2>
    <p>
      Welcome to the comprehensive web guide to User Cost Accounting, based on the peer-reviewed work of Khaled Aldhaferi (<em>JFA, 2025</em>).
      This site provides in-depth, actionable insights into a novel, value-based framework for resource accounting—designed to inform policy, corporate strategy, and academic research.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Why User Cost?</strong> Because conventional approaches systematically undervalue public resources and fail to secure intergenerational equity.</li>
      <li><strong>What’s new?</strong> The first operational model for <em>sustainability-weighted cost of capital</em> (SWACC), integrating user-cost theory, ESG risk, and real policy levers.</li>
      <li>Every page includes full explanations, formulas, and real-world implications—empowering you to understand, teach, and apply the framework.</li>
    </ul>
